# Cursor IDE Rules

## Language Rules
- Always write code in English
- All variable names, function names, class names must be in English
- All comments must be in English
- All user-facing strings, error messages, and UI text must be in English
- All documentation and README files must be in English
- All commit messages should be in English

## Code Style
- Use descriptive English names for variables and functions
- Write clear English comments for complex logic
- Use English for all console.log messages and debugging output
- Error messages and alerts should be in English

## Examples of what NOT to do:
❌ const nomeUsuario = "João"
❌ function criarPergunta() {}
❌ // Esta função calcula o hash
❌ alert("Erro ao processar")

## Examples of what TO do:
✅ const userName = "John"
✅ function createQuestion() {}
✅ // This function calculates the hash
✅ alert("Error processing request")
